sec.p:
Nitrogen fixation is the conversion of molecular nitrogen (N2) to ammonia, a more accessible nitrogen source for most organisms. Biological nitrogen fixation is catalyzed by nitrogenase, which can be classified into three isoforms according to metal contents in the catalytic components: MoFe-nitrogenase1, VFe-nitrogenase2,3, and FeFe-nitrogenase4,5. MoFe-nitrogenase has been most extensively studied6–8, and the reaction catalyzed by MoFe-nitrogenase is as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
